{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17493061","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17493061"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T06:54:25+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T06:54:25+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1211"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1211","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1211"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.05,0.09,0.07,0.28,0.52]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1211"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"103536"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1211","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1211"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1211"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"85952"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"1"},{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"43"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"98"},{"type":"tags","id":"539"},{"type":"tags","id":"1453"},{"type":"tags","id":"1812"},{"type":"tags","id":"4578"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"5771"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"7914"},{"type":"contributions","id":"8037"},{"type":"contributions","id":"13831"},{"type":"contributions","id":"15684"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19141"},{"type":"contributions","id":"28865"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"103536","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/103536"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 55-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic for pre-operative assessment prior to a planned admission for a laparoscopic cholecystectomy. She has a history of upper abdominal pain and was diagnosed with biliary colic. Her medical history includes type 2 diabetes, hypercholesterolaemia, and hypertension. She takes perindopril, atorvastatin, empagliflozin, ginseng, and fish oil. On examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. She is advised that some medications can increase the risk of bleeding and should be stopped prior to surgery.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following medications should be ceased prior to surgery to reduce bleeding risk?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Atorvastatin","Empagliflozin","Perindopril","Fish oil capsules","Ginseng"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EComplementary medicines are in common use in the general population. Medical practitioners must be aware of this and if necessary, counsel patients on cessation of their use when various medications or procedures are being considered.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGinseng\u003C/strong\u003E, which is used for type 2 diabetes, should be stopped prior to surgery in this patient as it increases the risk of post-operative bleeding. Ginseng is a herb used by people for type 2 diabetes, memory problems, fatigue, menopause symptoms, and as a dietary supplement, but its benefits have yet to be proven.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAtorvastatin\u003C/strong\u003E is a statin used to lower abnormally high lipid levels and for the prevention of cardiovascular diseases. It has no known untoward side effects in a patient who is about to undergo surgery.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEmpagliflozin\u003C/strong\u003E is a sodium-glucose co-transporter 2 inhibitor used for type 2 diabetes. While it should be withheld on the day of surgery due to the risk of euglycaemic diabetic ketoacidosis, it does not increase bleeding risk and is not the most relevant medication to cease for this reason.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPerindopril\u003C/strong\u003E is an ACE inhibitor used as an antihypertensive agent. It does not have any side effects that would impact this patient after a cholecystectomy. If the patient was having major surgery, where hypotension was a risk, then stopping the ACE inhibitor pre-operatively would be important. That is unlikely to be the case with a cholecystectomy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFish oil capsules\u003C/strong\u003E contain omega-3 polyunsaturated fatty acids that work by lowering the body\u0027s production of triglycerides. While there was previously some concern regarding increased bleeding while on fish oil tablets, several more recent studies have demonstrated no such risk in the peri-operative period. This medication is therefore safe to continue.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Ginseng, a herb used for type 2 diabetes, can increase the risk of post-operative bleeding."],"references":["Coon JT, Ernst E. Panax ginseng: A systematic review of adverse effects and drug interactions. Drug Saf. 2002;25:323\u201344. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/12020172/","Akintoye E, Sethi P, Harris W. Fish oil and perioperative bleeding: Insights from the OPERA randomized trial. Circulation: Cardiovacular Quality and Outcomes. 2018;11(11). Available at: https://www.ahajournals.org/doi/10.1161/CIRCOUTCOMES.118.004584"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"85952"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1211"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"85952","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/85952"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-05-23T14:18:02+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-05-23T14:18:02+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1211"}},"content":{"data":{"type